Marine Habitat Diversity Index (MHDI) for PA. The MHDI measures the bathymetric complexity of marine and coastal protected areas, expressed as variation in the vertical relief (derived from GEBCO elevation dataset). The MHDI can serve as a proxy of habitat complexity and diversity. Being the logarithm of the standard deviation of the bathymetry, it is dimensionless.
